t with all the friends i have made and the general attitude of Silver Hawks I will never leave Silver Hawks.<br>
<br>
 Silver Hawks is based on family and friends not &quot;UBER&quot; or the attitude  &quot;who ever has the most stuff wins&quot;. It is a pure joy to belong to such a fine guild with, IMHO, one of the best reputations in the game. It dose not matter what you have but how you play.<br>
<br>
If AA is breaking up, I would think that maybe greed might play a big part in it, I have some close friends in AA, and I know how they play.( they were not greedy but one only of they has time to group with me now) I also know that some of the old AA members did not like the fact that so many of DV came over at once, (again that greed thing, to many peeps not enough loot). Just to show u that even one of the most mighty guilds in the game can be taken down by a little green monster.<br>
<br>
Just my 2 cents<br>
<br>
