<br>
<br>
I troll on your board from time to time b/c of my contacts that I have here <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
there were a lot of things that pulled the guild to its end. Im not going into details but I will give you an overview. AA is a large guild some 90 active members **like every day raid active** the leadership is very very good but they tried to run the whole guild on about 4 sets of shouldiers. instead of breaking the guild up some.. <br>
<br>
example.. Fires of Heaven. they have guild leadership but they have Class leadership as well. the chanters take their biatches to one of two chanter leaders. and then if it is important enough those chanters take their concerns to the guild leadership. this also works in reverse, should the guild leader have a problem or need something from the chanters he would goto the chanter leaders.<br>
<br>
there was also an issue with faction, we were on ToV faction and some of our lvl 60 players wanted to switch over to Kael faction this caused some problems.<br>
<br>
Our Guild application process was too easy. if a person was up for membership the guild was supposed to vote yes or no for that person. and often times only like 10-20 people would vote **of a 150 approx membership** then the leaders would just choose, IMO based on class need this brought some undesierables into the guild.. <br>
<br>
Advice on guild application: make it a manditory thing for guild members to vote on new members dont make it a yes or no but a yes, no or dont know them. if they dont have 75% Yes then make them hang out with the guild more until they get that amount. <br>
<br>
and lastly b/c the guild leaders had all the strain on them they got tired and worn out this caused our demise..<br>
<br>
<br>
with Reguards,<br>
<br>
Baron Aelstyn Melarn<br>
Sorcerer *Epic*<br>
Proud Inmate of the Asylum<br>
